properties.name: Identity
properties.description: Core identifiers for study, site, subject

properties.name: Demographics
properties.description: Subject demographic characteristics

properties.name: Parameter
properties.description: Analysis parameter definitions

properties.name: Value
properties.description: Observation and analysis values

properties.name: Qualifier
properties.description: Type and method qualifiers

properties.name: Timing
properties.description: Temporal concepts and hierarchy

properties.name: Treatment
properties.description: Treatment assignment and dosing

properties.name: Flag
properties.description: Population and record flags

properties.name: Toxicity_Range
properties.description: Toxicity grading and reference ranges

properties.name: Time_to_Event
properties.description: Survival analysis concepts

properties.name: Traceability
properties.description: Source data traceability

properties.name: study
properties.description: Clinical study identifier

properties.name: site
properties.pattern: SITEGRy = pooled group y (e.g., SITEGR1, SITEGR2)
properties.description: Site identifier and pooled site groupings for analysis

properties.name: region
properties.pattern: REGIONy = region group y (e.g., REGION1, REGION2)
properties.description: Geographic region groupings

properties.name: subject
properties.description: Unique subject identifier. USUBJID is unique across studies, SUBJID is unique within study.

properties.name: sequence
properties.description: Analysis sequence number to ensure uniqueness within dataset

properties.name: disposition
properties.description: Trial disposition. EOS*=end of study, EOT*=end of treatment, EOP*=end of period, DC*=discontinuation reason

properties.name: milestone_date
properties.description: Key milestone dates. RFICDT=informed consent, ENRLDT=enrollment, RANDDT=randomization, LSTALVDT=last known alive, DTHDT=death

properties.name: death
properties.description: Death information. DTHDT=death date, DTHCAUS=cause, DTHCGRy=cause grouping y

properties.name: stratification
properties.description: Stratification factors. STRATAR=randomized stratum, STRATwR=stratum w randomized, STRATwV=stratum w value

properties.name: age
properties.pattern: AGEGRy = age group y (e.g., AGEGR1, AGEGR2)
properties.description: Subject age and age groupings. AAGE = derived analysis age, AGEGRy = age group y

properties.name: sex
properties.description: Subject sex

properties.name: race
properties.pattern: RACEGRy = race group y (e.g., RACEGR1, RACEGR2)
properties.description: Subject race and race groupings

properties.name: parameter
properties.pattern: PARCATy = parameter category y for grouping
properties.description: Analysis parameter and categorizations. PARAMCD limited to 8 characters.

properties.name: criteria
properties.description: Analysis parameter criteria. CRITy = criterion definition, CRITyFL = criterion met flag, MCRITy = multiple criteria

properties.name: observation_value
properties.description: Raw/collected observation value from SDTM source domains. Not stored directly in ADaM but is the source for AVAL.

properties.name: analysis_value
properties.description: Analysis value for parameter. AVAL = numeric, AVALC = character, AVALCATy = categorization

properties.name: baseline_value
properties.description: Subject baseline value. BASE = numeric, BASEC = character, BASECATy = categorization

properties.name: change_value
properties.description: Change from/to baseline. CHG = AVAL - BASE (from baseline), BCHG = BASE - AVAL (to baseline)

properties.name: percent_change
properties.description: Percent change from/to baseline. PCHG = ((AVAL-BASE)/BASE)*100

properties.name: ratio_value
properties.description: Ratio to reference value. R2BASE = AVAL/BASE, R2AyLO = ratio to lower limit, R2AyHI = ratio to upper limit

properties.name: shift_value
properties.description: Shift between defined pairings (e.g., Normal→High, Low→Normal)

properties.name: derivation_type
properties.description: Analysis value derivation method

properties.name: baseline_type
properties.description: Definition of baseline used when multiple baseline definitions exist

properties.name: treatment_type
properties.description: Distinguishes planned vs actual treatment (P = Planned, A = Actual)

properties.name: imputation_flag
properties.description: Date/time imputation flags indicating which components were imputed

properties.name: timepoint
properties.description: Analysis date/time/day. ADT = analysis date, ATM = analysis time, ADTM = datetime, ADY = relative day

properties.name: start_end_timepoint
properties.description: Start/end dates for intervals. AST* = analysis start, AEN* = analysis end

properties.name: visit
properties.description: Analysis visit and timepoint. AVISIT = visit description, ATPT = timepoint description, ATPTREF = reference

properties.name: period
properties.description: Analysis period and subperiod. APERIOD = period number, APERIODC = description, ASPER = subperiod

properties.name: phase
properties.description: Study phase categorization

properties.name: analysis_window
properties.description: Visit windowing parameters. AWTARGET = target day, AWLO/AWHI = window bounds, AWU = units

properties.name: relative_time
properties.description: Relative time from reference point. ARELTM = relative time value, ARELTMU = units

properties.name: period_timing_subject
properties.pattern: xx = period number (01, 02), w = phase number
properties.description: Subject-level period/phase start/end timing (ADSL). APxx* = period xx timing, PHw* = phase w timing

properties.name: period_timing_record
properties.description: Record-level period/subperiod/phase timing (BDS). APER* = period, ASPR* = subperiod, PH* = phase

properties.name: treatment_subject
properties.description: Subject-level treatment. TRTxxP/A = planned/actual for period xx, TRxxPGy = pooled group y, TRTSEQ* = treatment sequence

properties.name: treatment_record
properties.description: Record-level treatment. TRTP/TRTA = planned/actual treatment for record, TRTPGy/TRTAGy = pooled groups

properties.name: dose_subject
properties.description: Subject-level dose for period. DOSExxP = planned dose, DOSExxA = actual dose, DOSExxU = units

properties.name: dose_record
properties.description: Record-level dose. DOSEP/DOSEA = planned/actual dose, DOSCUMP/DOSCUMA = cumulative dose

properties.name: treatment_timing
properties.description: Treatment start/end timing. TRTS* = overall start, TRTE* = overall end, TRxx* = period xx timing

properties.name: treatment_duration
properties.description: Treatment duration. *DURD = days, *DURM = months, *DURY = years

properties.name: treatment_compliance
properties.description: Treatment compliance. TRCMP=compliance value, TRCMPGy=compliance grouping y

properties.name: population_flag
properties.description: Subject-level population flags. SAFFL=Safety, FASFL=Full Analysis Set, ITTFL=Intent-to-Treat, PPROTFL=Per-Protocol, COMPLFL=Completers, RANDFL=Randomized, ENRLFL=Enrolled

properties.name: record_population_flag
properties.description: Record-level population flags. *RFL = record in population by period, *PFL = record in population by parameter

properties.name: record_flag
properties.description: Record-level analysis flags. ABLFL=baseline record, ANLzzFL=analysis flag zz, ONTRTFL=on treatment, LVOTFL=last value on treatment

properties.name: toxicity_grade
properties.description: Toxicity grading. ATOXGR=analysis grade, BTOXGR=baseline grade, *L/*H=low/high direction

properties.name: analysis_range
properties.description: Normal/analysis ranges. ANRIND=normal range indicator, ANRLO/ANRHI=normal bounds, Ay*=analysis range y

properties.name: tte_origin
properties.description: Time-to-event origin point (when subject entered risk)

properties.name: censor
properties.description: Censoring indicator. CNSR=0 (event) or 1 (censored), EVNTDESC=event description, CNSDTDSC=censor date description

properties.name: source
properties.description: Datapoint traceability. SRCDOM=source domain, SRCVAR=source variable, SRCSEQ=source sequence
